Yes, the flickering of the screen can be minimized in the context of Graphics2D by using double buffering. Double buffering involves drawing the components of the window on an off-screen buffer and then transferring the completed buffer to the screen at once, reducing the flickering effect.

To implement double buffering in your code, you can modify the `NumberRainfall` class as follows:

```java
public class NumberRainfall extends JPanel {

    // ...

    public NumberRainfall(int numRectangles) {
        setDoubleBuffered(true); // Enable double buffering for the panel

        // ...
    }

    @Override
    protected void paintComponent(Graphics g) {
        super.paintComponent(g);

        Graphics2D g2d = (Graphics2D) g;

        // Create off-screen buffer
        BufferedImage offScreenBuffer = new BufferedImage(getWidth(), getHeight(), BufferedImage.TYPE_INT_ARGB);
        Graphics2D offScreenGraphics = offScreenBuffer.createGraphics();

        offScreenGraphics.setRenderingHint(RenderingHints.KEY_ANTIALIASING, RenderingHints.VALUE_ANTIALIAS_ON);

        for (Rectangle rectangle : rectangles) {
            offScreenGraphics.fillRect(rectangle.getXPosition(), rectangle.getYPosition(), RECT_WIDTH, RECT_HEIGHT);
        }

        // Transfer the completed buffer to the screen
        g2d.drawImage(offScreenBuffer, 0, 0, null);
    }

    // ...
}
```

In this updated code, the `NumberRainfall` class is now double buffered by enabling double buffering for the panel using the `setDoubleBuffered(true)` method. Additionally, a new off-screen buffer is created using a `BufferedImage` and all the drawing operations are performed on this off-screen buffer using a separate `Graphics2D` object (`offScreenGraphics`). Finally, the completed off-screen buffer is transferred to the screen using the `drawImage` method of the main `Graphics2D` object (`g2d`).

By implementing double buffering, the flickering on the screen should be minimized as the entire image is drawn off-screen and then transferred to the screen in a single step.

